observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:
Formulate clear, specific standard guidelines for hiring/rehiring personnel on job order/ casual/ contract of service to include, among others, the following:
• Conditions that would warrant the need for hiring/ rehiring of job order personnel;
• procedures in hiring;
• qualifications and other requirements;
• funding/applicable rates;
• incorporate in the contract the works to be performed, quantity and duration and submit quantified accomplishment reports; and
• requesting and approving authorities.
b. Coordinate with the Department Heads, particularly the HRMO, to assess and review the necessity of hiring job orders in order to maximize the services of permanent employees and at the same time minimize expenses on job order personnel.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Accountant to draw the necessary adjusting journal entries to arrive at the correct balance of the various Inventory and Expense accounts. Thus, the accounting policy on proper reporting and recording procedures will be properly observed.
We recommended further that the:
a. the Municipal Treasurer to record the issuances based on the RIS and to provide the SSMI and RIS to the Accounting Office to be used as basis in recording issuances of supplies and materials to the end users;
b. Inventory Committee to conduct physical count on all inventory items and submit the resulting Report of Physical Count of Inventories;
c. Municipal Treasurer and department concern to maintain and update stock cards for all inventory items under their jurisdiction; and
d. Municipal Accountant and Supply Officer to reconcile their respective records on inventory.

We have recommended that management:

Adopt earlier schedule of the municipality's budgeting activities considering the timelines of the enactment and approval of the annual municipal budget and its subsequent review by the SB;  

Require the BAC to prepare a Procurement Monitoring Report (PMR) in its prescribed format for approval and submission by the Municipal Mayor;

Require the MEO to collaborate with the MPDO, MBO and the Accounting Office in order to generate comprehensive and comparable reports; and    

Conduct a study every end of the year to identify projects that are no longer feasible for implementation and re-appropriate them to projects that will cater to the present needs of the community.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant: 

 install control measures to see to it that journal entries are properly taken up in the books in accordance with GAAP; 

effect the following proposed adjusting entries to correct the balance of the affected accounts.

We recommended that:

The Municipal Accountant ensure that all claims are adequately documented to establish their validity and regularity;
Management submit the master list and acknowledgement of receipt of the 630 knap sack sprayers by the farmer beneficiaries;


The BAC who is directly responsible for the procurement to explain in writing why the Inspection and Acceptance of the purchased knap sacks has been made when the procurement process was not yet complete in violation of the Implementing Rules and Regulations of the Republic Act 9184 otherwise known as the “Government Procurement Reform Act”, thus, the contract cost and the winning bidder was already pre-determined prior to the procurement process.
